We have developed and are distributing the following (stable) tools

* <a href="asmee.html">Asmee:</a> an editor for ASMs written in the AsmetaL language
* <a href="asmetalc.html">AsmetaLc:</a> a compiler/parser for AsmetaL models
* <a href="asmetas.html">AsmetaS:</a> a simulator
* <a href="asmetav.html">AsmetaV</a>: a scenario-based validator
* <a href="asmetaA.html">AsmetaA:</a> an execution animator
* <a href="asmetasmv.html">AsmetaSMV</a>: a model checker based on NuSMV
* <a href="asmetama.html">AsmetaMA</a>: a model advisor
* <a href="asmetavis.html">AsmetaVis</a>: a graphical visualizer of AsmetaL models
* <a href="asmrefprover.html">AsmetaRefProver</a>: a prover of refinement correctness
* <a href="asm2SMT.html">Asm2SMT</a>: a translator from AsmetaL models to Yices logical contexts
* <a href="asm2c++.html">Asm2C++</a>: a code generator


Some tools are provided both as eclipse plugins and standalone jars that can be executed at command line. Some are only available as jar files.

## Installing ASMETA in eclipse

Some ASMETA tools are integrated in eclipse. The update site is <b>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/asmeta/asmeta_update_site/master</b>.
Perform the following steps to install an Asmeta tool from the update site:
<p><b>1. From your Eclipse menu select <i>Help</i> <i>Software Updates</i>
<i>Find and Install...</i></b></p>
<p><b>2. Check <i>Search for new features</i> and press <i>Next</i>.</b>
</p>
<p><b>3. Press <i>New Remote Site...</i> and enter
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/asmeta/asmeta_update_site/master for the update site URL</b></p>
<p><b>4. Press <i>Finish</i>.</b></p>
<p><b>5. Select the desired tool(s).</b></p>
<p><b>6. Follow the steps in the installation wizard.</b></p>


